The paper deals with algorithms for finding convex sets containing a balanced number of red and blue points in a two-colored point set in the plane. This problem is closely related to computational geometry (cs.CG) and discrete mathematics (cs.DM). The algorithms presented in the paper involve data structures and computational complexity, which are also relevant to computer science theory (cs.CC) and graph theory (cs.GT). Additionally, the paper mentions the use of logarithmic time algorithms, which suggests that algorithms and data structures (cs.DS) may also be relevant.
